thinserverEnable.name: thinserverEnable
thinserverEnable.description: This device provides thin server support. If enabled(1) then this device will provide local file caching of selected files. If passthru(2) then this device will have connections to the clients and pass any frames received on those connections to the master server and pass frames received from the master server to the appropriate client. If disabled(0) then the clients will contact the master server directly. If disabledpending(3), then thin server support is in the process of disabling.

thinserverRefreshInterval.name: thinserverRefreshInterval
thinserverRefreshInterval.description: This is the number of days between refreshes of this devices cache.

thinserverRefreshTime.name: thinserverRefreshTime
thinserverRefreshTime.description: This is the time of day (12:01:00) at which this device will verify that it has the same version of the files as the master server, and will download any files which are not the same version.

thinserverRefreshNow.name: thinserverRefreshNow
thinserverRefreshNow.description: This flag indicates that the device should immediately refresh all files which it is caching. A read of this object will always return noaction(1).

thinserverMemory.name: thinserverMemory
thinserverMemory.description: This is the amount of memory in kilobytes calculated at runtime to be reserved for caching files. This may be the same amount as the configured memory.

thinserverHardFileSpace.name: thinserverHardFileSpace
thinserverHardFileSpace.description: This is the total amount of hard file space, in kilobytes, which can be used for the files being cached for the thin server function.

thinserverHardFileUsed.name: thinserverHardFileUsed
thinserverHardFileUsed.description: This is the total amount of hard file space, in kilobytes, which is currently being used for the files related to the thin server function.

thinserverNumFilesCached.name: thinserverNumFilesCached
thinserverNumFilesCached.description: This is the total number of files being cached by the thin server function.

thinserverMasterServerIPAddress.name: thinserverMasterServerIPAddress
thinserverMasterServerIPAddress.description: This is the IP address of the server for which this device is staging files.

thinserverSyncProtocol.name: thinserverSyncProtocol
thinserverSyncProtocol.description: This is the protocol which will be used to determine whether or not the cache needs to be updated and if so, this protocol will be used to retrieve the new version of the file(s).

thinserverPreloadListName.name: thinserverPreloadListName
thinserverPreloadListName.description: This is the fully-qualified name of the file which contains the pre-load list. This name can be 1024 bytes long but only the last 255 bytes will be displayed.

thinserverMountPointsTable.name: thinserverMountPointsTable
thinserverMountPointsTable.description: When NFS is used as the synchronization protocol, then this table lists the directories to be included in the mount point from which files will be cached.

thinserverMountPointsEntry.name: thinserverMountPointsEntry
thinserverMountPointsEntry.description: An entry containing objects that define which directories are to be included for the mount point.

thinserverMountPointsIndex.name: thinserverMountPointsIndex
thinserverMountPointsIndex.description: A unique value for each mount point.

thinserverMountPointsDescr.name: thinserverMountPointsDescr
thinserverMountPointsDescr.description: A textual string containing the name of a mount point (NFS). This name can be 1024 bytes long, but only the last 255 bytes will be displayed.

thinserverMountPointsScope.name: thinserverMountPointsScope
thinserverMountPointsScope.description: If include(1), then that directory is included in the mount point. If exclude(2), then that directory is excluded from the mount point.

thinserverPacketTimeout.name: thinserverPacketTimeout
thinserverPacketTimeout.description: This is the number of seconds defined by the user until a packet will time out.

thinserverMaxRetries.name: thinserverMaxRetries
thinserverMaxRetries.description: This is the maximum number of times defined by the user that the TFTP daemon will try to resend a packet.

thinserverMaxSegSize.name: thinserverMaxSegSize
thinserverMaxSegSize.description: This is the maximum segment block size defined by the user.

thinserverUseHardFile.name: thinserverUseHardFile
thinserverUseHardFile.description: This tells whether or not we are to use the hardfile when caching.

thinserverRestartNow.name: thinserverRestartNow
thinserverRestartNow.description: This flag indicates that the device should immediately restart the thinserver feature. A read of this object will always return noaction(1).

thinserverConfiguredMemory.name: thinserverConfiguredMemory
thinserverConfiguredMemory.description: This is the amount of memory in kilobytes defined by the user to be reserved for caching files.

thinserverFilesOpenCurrently.name: thinserverFilesOpenCurrently
thinserverFilesOpenCurrently.description: This is the number of files currently in the open state because of the thin server function.

thinserverTotalFileOpens.name: thinserverTotalFileOpens
thinserverTotalFileOpens.description: This is the total number of files that have been opened since the last reset of the genStat counters because of the thin server function.

thinserverReadMissesDirty.name: thinserverReadMissesDirty
thinserverReadMissesDirty.description: Number of times a read was relayed to the server because the file on this device is different than the version on the master server.

thinserverReadMissesNotPresent.name: thinserverReadMissesNotPresent
thinserverReadMissesNotPresent.description: Number of times a read was relayed to the server because this device does not have the desired file.

thinserverOpenFailsFileLocked.name: thinserverOpenFailsFileLocked
thinserverOpenFailsFileLocked.description: Number of times a read was relayed to the server because this device cannot serve the desired file because it is locked.

thinserverNoRoomOnHardFile.name: thinserverNoRoomOnHardFile
thinserverNoRoomOnHardFile.description: Number of times the thin server function attempted to cache a file but could not because there was no more thin server space available on the hard disk.

thinserverResetGenCounters.name: thinserverResetGenCounters
thinserverResetGenCounters.description: Reset the general counters to zero. A read of this object will always return noaction(1).

thinserverNumRefreshes.name: thinserverNumRefreshes
thinserverNumRefreshes.description: Number of times the cache has been successfully refreshed.

thinserverNumRefreshFail.name: thinserverNumRefreshFail
thinserverNumRefreshFail.description: Number of times the cache has failed to refresh because the connection to the master server could not be established.

thinserverNumFilesRefreshed.name: thinserverNumFilesRefreshed
thinserverNumFilesRefreshed.description: Number of files which have been refreshed in the cache.

thinserverLastFileUpdate.name: thinserverLastFileUpdate
thinserverLastFileUpdate.description: This is the date and time of day (02/03/1998 23:08:09) that the most recent file refresh occurred.

thinserverResetMSConnStats.name: thinserverResetMSConnStats
thinserverResetMSConnStats.description: Reset the MS connection counters to zero. A read of this object will always return noaction(1).

thinserverRFSTotalClients.name: thinserverRFSTotalClients
thinserverRFSTotalClients.description: The number of clients which have connected to this device using RFS/400 protocol.

thinserverRFSCurrentClients.name: thinserverRFSCurrentClients
thinserverRFSCurrentClients.description: The number of clients currently connected to this device using RFS/400 protocol.

thinserverRFSFilesServed.name: thinserverRFSFilesServed
thinserverRFSFilesServed.description: This is the number of open requests for which this device opened a cached file.

thinserverRFSFilesServedByMS.name: thinserverRFSFilesServedByMS
thinserverRFSFilesServedByMS.description: This is the number of open requests for which this device has passed the request thru to the master server because the local copy either does not exist, is out-of-date, or is not accessable.

thinserverNum449Accepts.name: thinserverNum449Accepts
thinserverNum449Accepts.description: The number of port 449 (port mapper) accepts.

thinserverNum449ConnsActive.name: thinserverNum449ConnsActive
thinserverNum449ConnsActive.description: The number of port 449 (port mapper) connections currently active.

thinserverNum8473Accepts.name: thinserverNum8473Accepts
thinserverNum8473Accepts.description: The number of port 8473 (RFS server) accepts.

thinserverNum8473ConnsActive.name: thinserverNum8473ConnsActive
thinserverNum8473ConnsActive.description: The number of port 8473 (RFS server) connections currently active.

thinserverNum8476Accepts.name: thinserverNum8476Accepts
thinserverNum8476Accepts.description: The number of port 8476 (Login server) accepts.

thinserverNum8476ConnsActive.name: thinserverNum8476ConnsActive
thinserverNum8476ConnsActive.description: The number of port 8476 (Login server) connections currently active.

thinserverNumRFSWrites.name: thinserverNumRFSWrites
thinserverNumRFSWrites.description: The number of attempts to write to a file being cached. The write and all future accesses to that file (until it is closed) will be relayed to the server.

thinserverResetRFSCounters.name: thinserverResetRFSCounters
thinserverResetRFSCounters.description: Reset the RFS counters to zero. A read of this object will always return noaction(1).

thinserverTFTPTotalClients.name: thinserverTFTPTotalClients
thinserverTFTPTotalClients.description: The number of clients which have connected to this device using TFTP protocol.

thinserverTFTPCurrentClients.name: thinserverTFTPCurrentClients
thinserverTFTPCurrentClients.description: The number of clients currently connected to this device using TFTP protocol.

thinserverTFTPFileisServed.name: thinserverTFTPFileisServed
thinserverTFTPFileisServed.description: This is the number of open requests for which this device opened a cached file.

thinserverTFTPFilesServedByMS.name: thinserverTFTPFilesServedByMS
thinserverTFTPFilesServedByMS.description: This is the number of open requests for which this device has passed the request thru to the master server because the local copy either does not exist, is out-of-date, or is not accessable.

thinserverResetTFTPCounters.name: thinserverResetTFTPCounters
thinserverResetTFTPCounters.description: Reset the TFTP counters to zero. A read of this object will always return noaction(1).

thinserverNFSDReadRequests.name: thinserverNFSDReadRequests
thinserverNFSDReadRequests.description: The total number of READ requests received from NFS clients.

thinserverNFSDReadDirRequests.name: thinserverNFSDReadDirRequests
thinserverNFSDReadDirRequests.description: The total number of READDIR requests received from NFS clients.

thinserverNFSDUnsupportedRequests.name: thinserverNFSDUnsupportedRequests
thinserverNFSDUnsupportedRequests.description: This is the total number of requests for unsupported procedures received by NFS clients.

thinserverNFSDTotalMounts.name: thinserverNFSDTotalMounts
thinserverNFSDTotalMounts.description: This is the total number of succesful mount requests received from NFS clients.

thinserverNFSDCurrentMounts.name: thinserverNFSDCurrentMounts
thinserverNFSDCurrentMounts.description: The number of currently active mounts.

thinserverNFSDTotalClients.name: thinserverNFSDTotalClients
thinserverNFSDTotalClients.description: The total number of clients that have successfully mounted to the NFS Server Mount Daemon.

thinserverNFSDCurrentClients.name: thinserverNFSDCurrentClients
thinserverNFSDCurrentClients.description: The current number of clients that have active mounts to the NFS Server Mount Daemon.

thinserverNFSDResetCounters.name: thinserverNFSDResetCounters
thinserverNFSDResetCounters.description: Reset the NFSD counters to zero. A read of this object will always return noaction(1).
